<subSubSection pageId="6" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1436,151,573]" pageId="6" pageNumber="31">
[TL: 
<collectingCountry box="[725,859,331,357]" name="Kazakhstan" pageId="6" pageNumber="31">Kazakhstan</collectingCountry>
, Taldi Kurgan and mountains near Issyk-Kul Lake and Ili River], name preoccupied by 
<taxonomicName authority="Staudinger, 1881" authorityName="Staudinger" authorityYear="1881" box="[556,1009,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="parthenie" subSpecies="alatauica">
<emphasis box="[556,812,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="31">M. parthenie alatauica</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Staudinger, O." box="[817,1009,367,393]" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" pagination="193 - 215" refId="ref11194" refString="Staudinger, O. (1881) Beitrag zur Lepidopterenfauna Central-Asiens. Stettin Entomologischen Zeitung, 42 (7 - 9), 193 - 215 + 253 - 300." type="journal article" year="1881">Staudinger, 1881</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. The name was replaced by 
<taxonomicName authority="Wnukowsky, 1929" authorityName="Wnukowsky" authorityYear="1929" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subSpecies" species="phoebe" subSpecies="wagneri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="31">M. phoebe wagneri</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Wnukowsky, W." box="[248,459,403,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" pagination="221 - 224" refId="ref12039" refString="Wnukowsky, W. (1929) Einige faunistische Angaben uber die Insekten Siberiens und des Ussuri-Gebietes. Zoologischer Anzeiger, 83 (9 / 10), 221 - 224." type="journal article" year="1929">Wnukowsky, 1929</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. Male specimens of this 
<taxonomicName box="[730,905,403,429]" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" rank="variety" variety="together">variety together</taxonomicName>
with typical 
<taxonomicName box="[1048,1165,403,429]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis box="[1048,1165,403,429]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="31">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were figured by 
<bibRefCitation author="Wagner, F." pageId="6" pageNumber="31" pagination="22 - 288" refId="ref11971" refString="Wagner, F. (1913) Beitrag zur Lepidopterenfauna des Iligebietes sowie des Sary-Dschas (Asia centr.) Entomologische Mitteilungen Berlin, 2 (5), 22 - 288." type="journal article" year="1913">Wagner (1913: 89</bibRefCitation>
, figs 5 &amp; 6), exemplifying the heavy post discal black spotting, differentiating it from typical 
<taxonomicName box="[1311,1429,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="phoebe">
<emphasis box="[1311,1429,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="31">M. phoebe</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. This variety is included here because 
<bibRefCitation author="Higgins, L. G." box="[570,796,475,501]" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" pagination="175 - 365" refId="ref9372" refString="Higgins, L. G. (1941) An illustrated catalogue of the Palearctic Melitaea (Lep. Rhopalocera). Transactions of the Royal Entomological Society of London, 91, 175 - 365. https: // doi. org / 10.1111 / j. 1365 - 2311.1941. tb 01045. x" type="journal article" year="1941">Higgins (1941: 338)</bibRefCitation>
suggested it might be referable to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alpheraky" authorityYear="1881" box="[1181,1286,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibina">
<emphasis box="[1181,1286,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="31">M. sibina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It was noted above that 
<bibRefCitation author="Toth, J. P. &amp; Varga, Z." box="[274,508,511,537]" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" pagination="258 - 268" refId="ref11248" refString="Toth, J. P. &amp; Varga, Z. (2011) Inter- and intraspecific variation in the genitalia of the ' Melitaea phoebe group' (Lepidoptera. Nymphalidae). Zoologischer Anzeiger, 250, 258 - 268. [6 pp. of Appendix with key and figures of genitalia only present in the on-line version, www. sciencedirect. com] https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. jcz. 2011.05.002" type="book chapter" year="2011">Tóth &amp; Varga (2011)</bibRefCitation>
were unable to separate these two species; however, the present authors accept the taxon 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Alpheraky" authorityYear="1881" box="[220,288,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Nymphalidae" genus="Melitaea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sibina">
<emphasis box="[220,288,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="31">sibina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
at species level.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
